That’s 1,424 times the median pay of a Disney worker.
To put that gap in context, in 1978, the average CEO made about 30 times a typical worker’s salary.
Since 1978, CEO pay has grown by 937 percent, while the pay of an average worker grew just 11.2 percent.
As billions of dollars landed in the laps of management, they spent as a rule not on their workforces but on wealth-enriching strategies such as stock buybacks and, yes, executive pay.
Disney has pushed back by noting that it pays more than the $7.25 federal minimum wage.